@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: Admin Views Research Details

actor Admin
participant "Frontend/UI" as UI
participant "Backend/API" as API
participant "Auth Middleware (JWT)" as AUTH
participant "Service Layer" as SERVICE
database "Database (Neon)" as DB
participant "Cache Layer (Optional)" as CACHE

== Open Research Details Page ==
Admin -> UI: Navigate to 'Research Details' page

UI -> API: GET /trl/case/{id} (JWT)
UI -> API: GET /trl/research/{id} (JWT)
UI -> API: GET /trl/coordinator/{id} (JWT)
UI -> API: GET /trl/assessment/{id} (JWT)
UI -> API: GET /trl/appointment/{id} (JWT)
UI -> API: GET /trl/ip/{id} (JWT)
UI -> API: GET /trl/supportment/{id}(JWT)

API -> AUTH: Verify JWT & role=Admin
AUTH --> API: Valid / Invalid

alt Invalid Token
    API --> UI: 401 Unauthorized
    UI --> Admin: Redirect to Login
else Valid
    API -> CACHE: Check cache (case details)
    alt Cache Hit
        CACHE --> API: Return cached details
    else Cache Miss
        API -> SERVICE: Aggregate research details

        SERVICE -> DB: Fetch case info
        SERVICE -> DB: Fetch researcher info
        SERVICE -> DB: Fetch coordinator info
        SERVICE -> DB: Fetch assessments
        SERVICE -> DB: Fetch appointments
        SERVICE -> DB: Fetch IP data
        SERVICE -> DB: Fetch supportment data

        DB --> SERVICE: Return all related data
        SERVICE --> API: Combined research detail object
        API -> CACHE: Store aggregated data (TTL 60s)
    end

    API --> UI: 200 OK (Full Research Details)
end

UI --> Admin: Render research details page
UI --> Admin: Display tabs (Assessment / IP / Appointment / Supportment)

@enduml